natural problem: Eight pounds of feathers and two ounces of gold together cost $\$932$. Fourteen pounds of feathers and three ounces of gold together cost $\$1402$. What is the cost of five pounds of feathers and five ounces of gold?
natural solution: Let $f$ be the cost of a pound of feathers and $g$ the cost of an ounce of gold.
We have \begin{align} 8f+2g&=932 \\ 14f+3g&=1402 \end{align}Solving the first equation for $g$ we get $g=466-4f$.
Substituting into the second equation, we solve \[ 14f+3(466-4f)=1402 \]to find $f=2$.
Thus five pounds of feathers and five ounces of gold costs $5(f+g)=\boxed{2300}$ dollars.
